(1, 'rooted-jazz-concert', '"Rooted" Jazz Concert', '', '', '', '<p>Friends and arts enthusiasts, I want to invite you out to a nice little jazz concert this Saturday evening that some of my friends will be featured in titled &ldquo;Rooted&rdquo;. I got to hear a preview of Dr. Terry&rsquo;s bass and trombone jazz composition &ldquo;Intersections&rdquo; and I&rsquo;d say the price of this concert is worth just hearing that again. In addition to him, there will be a wonderful line up of other jazz artists and original works presented, all ending with a jam session! Tickets are $8 online and $10 at the door. Do come on out for a fun evening of new music. Feel free to bring friends. Details below -</p>\r\n<h3><a href="http://www.loftartsproductions.com">Loft Arts Productions</a> Presents:</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nRooted Duo, Live in Manhattan - <a href="http://www.smarttix.com/show.aspx?EID=&amp;showCode=ROO38&amp;GUID=0c3b2282-d78e-4496-b0cd-cbca83982cf8">Event link</a><br />\r\nDr. Terry L. Greene II, trombone/composition<br />\r\nRebekah Griffin Greene, double bass/composition\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Saturday, February 27th, 8:00 PM<br />\r\nThe Chapel at the Church of St. Paul and St.Andrew<br />\r\n263 W 86th St (between Broadway and West End) New York, NY 10024</p>\r\n<p>Tickets are $10 at the door, and $8 (+ $1.50 service charge) if you buy them <a href="http://www.smarttix.com/show.aspx?EID=&amp;showCode=ROO38&amp;GUID=0c3b2282-d78e-4496-b0cd-cbca83982cf8">online</a></p>\r\n<h3>The program so far:</h3>\r\n<ul class="list outside disc">\r\n    <li>(S)weep - by Erica Ball, for violin and cello, featuring Fung Chern Hwei on violin.</li>\r\n    <li>Edge - for solo bass, by Peter Askim.</li>\r\n    <li> Intersections - by Terry L. Greene II, for trombone and bass.</li>\r\n    <li> Short Mass for String Trio - by Rebekah Griffin Greene, featuring Ina Litera, viola and Egil\r\n    Rostad cello</li>\r\n    <li>Jazz tunes TBA: Terry L. Greene II, trombone, Anna Katherine Montgomery, vocals, Avery Daily, drums, Moto, electric bass,\r\n    and some surprise jam session guests!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more info visit &ndash; <a href="http://www.rebekahgriffingreene.com">rebekahgriffingreene.com</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThanks for supporting live music and creativity!\r\n</p>', 'Friends and arts enthusiasts, I want to invite you out to a nice little jazz concert this Saturday evening that some of my friends will be featured in titled &ldquo;Rooted&rdquo;.', 0, '2010-02-25 00:00:00', '2010-02-25', '2014-05-31 14:05:10'),
(2, 'call-for-entries-excalibur-foundry-group-show', 'Call for Entries: Excalibur Foundry Group Show', '', '', '', '<h1>THE FIRST ANNUAL <a href="http://excaliburbronzeny.com">EXCALIBUR SCULPTURE FOUNDRY</a> GROUP SHOW: SCULPTURE 2010</h1>\r\n<h2>CALLING ALL SCULPTORS &ndash; SUBMIT YOUR BEST WORK NOW!</h2>\r\n<h3><a href="/assets/docs/Excalibur_Sculpture_Show_2010_entry_form.pdf">Download the prospectus and entry form</a></h3>\r\n<p>May 3 &ndash; May 14, 2010 Jury: Excalibur Sculpture Foundry Artists Entry Deadline: March 18, 2010 Excalibur Bronze Sculpture Foundry invites sculptors from around the world to submit up to 3 sculptures to the 1st annual juried Excalibur Group Show: SCULPTURE 2010 This international competition is open to both emerging as well as established artists and will be juried by the artists of Excalibur Bronze Sculpture Foundry.</p>\r\n<p>Established in 1967 as a small metal shop catering to artists in Manhattan&rsquo;s West Village, Excalibur has since developed into a full-service fine art foundry with clients around the world. The winning sculptors will be selected by the Excalibur Sculpture Foundry Artist Panel and their work will be featured in a two week show and special opening event in conjunction with the EXCALIBUR CANDLELIGHT BRONZE POUR. For the first time, Excalibur will open its doors to New York City at night during the show&rsquo;s opening party for a very special bronze pour exhibition presented by the venerable 43-year old bronze sculpture foundry in the burgeoning arts hub of Ridgewood / Bushwick in Brooklyn, NY.</p>\r\n<p>One Grand Prize winner will be announced at the opening and will receive a $2,500 credit for Excalibur bronze casting services such as mouldmaking, lost wax casting and/or patination of their work. All exhibitors will receive recognition on the Excalibur website consisiting of a photo of selected work and a link to their personal websites on the Excalibur website for the duration of the show.</p>\r\n<div class="hr">\r\n<h3>Eligibility:</h3>\r\n<p>Open to artists 18 years or older living in the US or internationally. Sculpture only please. All work must be original. Fees:<br />\r\nThe entry fee is $25. Kindly make checks payable to &ldquo;Excalibur Bronze Sculpture Foundry&rdquo; and mail with <a href="/assets/docs/Excalibur_Sculpture_Show_2010_entry_form.pdf"><br />\r\n</a><a href="http://excaliburbronzeny.com/page20.php">Click here for more information on the show</a></p>\r\n<p>Interested in learning more about Excalibur Sculpture Foundry or getting casting quotes? Visit - <a href="http://excaliburbronzeny.com">excaliburbronzeny.com</a></p>\r\n</div>', 'The first annual Excalibur Sculpture Foundry group show: Sculpture 2010  calling all sculptors!', 1, '2010-02-26 00:00:00', '2010-02-26', '2014-05-31 14:02:26'),
(3, 'call-for-submissions-benefit-art-auction', 'Call for Entries: Journey for Justin | Benefit Art Auction', '', '', '', '<p>Friday, December 17th 2010, 6:30pm-9:30pm<br />\r\n@ <a href="http://saltspacenyc.com">Salt Space</a> - 1158 Broadway New York, NY 10024\r\n</p>\r\n<p><br />\r\n</p>\r\n<h3>Call for Submission: <strong>*deadline December 3rd 2010</strong></h3>\r\n<p>\r\nDear Artists,<br />\r\nIn efforts to raise money to cover the critical medical expenses of our friend Justin Yuen, we are putting together an art auction. We are now collecting artwork for Journey for Justin&rsquo;s art auction and you are welcome to submit. All 2-D and 3-D fine art will be accepted for review. You may submit up to three works to be juried.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIf you are interested, send an email to <a href="mailto:submissions@journeyforjustin.com">submissions@journeyforjustin.com</a> with up to three images of each submitted artwork attached in the following format along with the following details -\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Image Format:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nSubmit Jpegs (.jpg) sized up to fit within a 700 x 700 pixel dimension saved at 300dpi.\r\nTitle each image with your name and then a sequential alpha-numeric append (for multiple pieces and views: 1a-c, 2a-c, 3a-c).<br />\r\n<strong>ex.</strong><br />\r\nJustinYuen_1a.jpg,<br />\r\nJustinYuen_1b.jpg,<br />\r\nJustinYuen_1c.jpg,<br />\r\nJustinYuen_2a.jpg,<br />\r\n&hellip;. JustinYuen_3c.jpg\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Details:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>- The Artist -</strong><br />\r\n1. Full name<br />\r\n2. Mailing address<br />\r\n3. Email address<br />\r\n4. Phone number<br />\r\n*5. Resume, artist statement, or brief bio  (*optional)\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>- For each submitted artwork -</strong><br />\r\n1. Title of work<br />\r\n2. Medium<br />\r\n3. Dimensions<br />\r\n4. Brief description<br />\r\n4. Starting bid price\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Sales:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nChecks in full for sold work will be made directly to the artist. We are suggesting (though not requiring) that a 70% donation of the price of sold works be gifted by the artist to Journey for Justin.\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Deadlines:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nThe deadline for work submission is December 3rd, 2010. Selected artists will be informed of accepted artwork by December 5th, 2010.  All artwork must be delivered to NYC for the show by December 15th, 2010.\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Delivery:</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nBoth in-person and mailed deliveries of work are allowed. Artists will be notified of the exact artwork delivery location/address in New York City upon selection. If mailing in artwork, appropriate return packaging and postage must be included. Journey for Justin is not responsible for return packaging or postage or liable for any delivery damage to work. All artwork not sold, will be returned to artist\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Thank you.</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n<strong>For more information please visit the following websites:</strong><br />\r\n<a href="http://www.journeyforjustin.com/blog/about/">- made by a couple of former colleagues in SanFransisco</a><br />\r\n<a href="http://justlive.posterous.com">- Justin''s personal blog he''s been recording since the journey began</a><br />\r\n<a href="http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=149816065058924">- Justin''s facebook support page</a>\r\n</p>', 'Dear artists, in an effort to raise money to cover the critical medical expenses of our friend Justin Yuen, we are putting together an art auction.', 1, '2010-10-21 00:00:00', '2010-10-21', '2014-05-31 13:54:46'),
(4, 'lic-arts-open', 'Event: Long Island City Arts Open', '', '', '', '<p>NYC&rsquo;s Fastest-Growing Creative Community to Celebrate Its Artistic Diversity with Weeklong Festival</p>\r\n<a href="http://www.licartsopen.org" target="_blank"><img alt="Long Island City Arts Open" src="http://www.licartsopen.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-05-10-at-4.31.24-PM.png" height="200" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<p><strong><a href="http://www.licartsopen.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/LICAO_Brochure_Web_2.pdf">DOWNLOAD THE BROCHURE</a> FOR ALL THE INFO!</strong></p>\r\n<p>The first annual <strong><a href="http://www.licartsopen.org" target="_blank">LIC Arts Open</a></strong>, an exciting celebration of the thriving arts community in <strong>Long Island City, Queens</strong>, will take place on <strong>May 14 &ndash; 22, 2011.</strong> This fabulous week will be open to the public and feature myriad cultural activities and events, many of them FREE, including:</p>\r\n<p>&bull; One of NYC&rsquo;s largest <strong>Artists Open Studios</strong> (May 21 &amp; 22), with hundreds of artists opening their studios for viewing at Reis Studios, LIC Art Center, Wills Studios, PaintCan Studios, Brickhouse Ceramics, Salazar Studios, Mittman, RealArt and more;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Special exhibitions</strong>, including a show in The Industry curated by Jeffrey Leder; Helaine Soller at Riverview Restaurant; Experimental Space group show curated by Michael Rodriguez @ Reis Studios; &ldquo;Edible Art LIC&rdquo;, a photography exhibit of some of the top LIC restaurants and their chefs, by Jesse Winter @ Ten10Studios;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Gallery shows of LIC artists</strong> at the spacious new Jeffrey Leder Gallery, M55 Gallery, the newly expanded Reis Gallery, Local Project, Ten10 Studios and other LIC venues;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Musical performances</strong> with renowned teachers from the LIC Academy of Music, Emmy award winner J. Walter Hawkes and Pat Irwin (formerly of the B-52s), Jazz with the Jonathan Parker Group, and other local musicians; experimental music with Random Access Music;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Theater</strong> including the Queens Fringe Festival, Face/Off Comedy Improv, Hyperion Theatre and Queens Shakespeare doing A Midsummer Nights Dream, Secret Burlesque, @ the Secret Theatre;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Dance performances</strong> by Octavia Cup Dance Theatre in the Metropolitan Building, Forward Motion Theatre (revision series) at Attic Studios, Insight Dance (modern), and students from the LIC School of Ballet;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Walking tours</strong> throughout the week led by Queens Borough historian Jack Eichenbaum;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Workshops, demonstrations, film screenings</strong>;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Food events</strong> via local culinary gems like M. Wells, LIC Market, Jassi&rsquo;s, Da Gianni&rsquo;s, Manducatis Rustica, Breadbox Cafe, Sage General Store and others, with <em>Edible Queens</em> involved;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Community outreach</strong> including an art contest for Queens K-12 students, adjudicated by Councilman Jimmy Van Bramer and prominent local artists;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>Kick-Off and Wrap Parties</strong> open to all;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; <strong>And much, much more</strong> to engage arts lovers of New York and beyond!</p>\r\n<p>&hellip; all just one subway stop away from Manhattan and Brooklyn!</p>\r\n<p><em>The LIC Arts Open is organized by the LIC Arts Open organization, a collaboration of arts entities, businesses and individuals seeking to spotlight the diverse artistic community in Long Island City, Queens. *LIC Arts Open is under the fiscal sponsorship of Fractured Atlas.</em></p>', 'The first annual LIC Arts Open, an exciting celebration of the thriving arts community in Long Island City, Queens, will take place on May 14 - 22, 2011.', 1, '2011-05-12 00:00:00', '2011-05-12', '2014-05-31 14:11:00'),
(5, 'sendnyc-silent-art-auction-mission-to-vietnam', 'Event: SendNYC Silent Art Auction | Mission To Vietnam', '', '', '', '<p>This Saturday you are invited to <a href="http://www.sendnyc.com">SendNYC&rsquo;s</a> silent auction to benefit the <a href="http://sendnyc.com/Auction/About">NYC 2nd Mission Team - Mission to Vietnam</a>. Come enjoy an evening of refreshments, performance, auction bidding and raffles hosted by the <a href="http://www.saltartspace.org">Salt Art Space</a>. All proceeds from the event will help the NYC 2nd MISSION team cover travel and lodging costs for their trip to Ho Chi Minh City. All are welcome. Doors open at 6:30pm.<br /><br />When: 11/14/09 Saturday @ 6:30pm (Don Nguyen&rsquo;s performance begins at 7:30pm).<br />Where: <a href="http://www.saltartspace.org">Salt Art Space</a> &ndash; 1160 Broadway @27th Street, fifth floor<br /><a href="http://sendnyc.com/Auction/Details">Learn More &amp; bid online! Click here.</a><br /><br />-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Join us for an evening of dramatic performance, silent auction, food, drink and raffles. The event will begin at 6:30 PM on November 14 at the Salt Art Space in New York City and will include a live reading from Don Nguyen&rsquo;s new play Red Flamboyant at 7:30 PM.Can&rsquo;t join us in New York for the auction? Bid online! Online bidding will begin on November 9.All proceeds from the event will help the NYC 2nd MISSION team cover travel and lodging costs for their trip to Ho Chi Minh City.<br />-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Salt Art Space - <a href="http://www.saltartspace.org">http://www.saltartspace.org</a><br />Gallery Church - <a href="http://www.gallerychurch.com">http://www.gallerychurch.com</a><br />SendNYC - <a href="http://www.sendnyc.com">http://www.sendnyc.com</a><br />Nomadic by design - <a href="http://www.nomadicbydesign.com">http://www.nomadicbydesign.com</a></p>', 'This Saturday you are invited to SendNYC&apos;s silent auction to benefit the NYC 2nd Mission Team - Mission to Vietnam.', 1, '2009-11-09 00:00:00', '2009-11-09', '2014-05-31 14:09:20'),
(6, 'sram-part-project-2012', 'Exhibition &amp; Auction: SRAM pART Project', '/images/post/sram-part-project-2012.jpg', 'SRAM pArt Project', '', '<p><a href="http://www.sram.com/partproject/about.php" target="_blank">SRAM pART PROJECT</a> transforms bike parts into art that makes a difference and a big splash, too.</p>\r\n<p>For the <a href="http://www.sram.com/partproject/new-york/overview.php" target="_blank">New York City event</a>, 95 noted artists will contribute original pieces created from SRAM components &ndash; including, for the first time, works of collage as well as sculpture. The artworks will be featured in a juried gallery exhibition, then sold at a gala live auction event. One hundred percent of the proceeds will be donated to <a href="http://worldbicyclerelief.org/pages/about" target="_blank">World Bicycle Relief</a>.</p>\r\n<p>First- and second-place prizes will be awarded in the collage and sculpture categories. There will also be one overall grand-prize winner, who will receive an all-expenses-paid trip for two to Africa to witness the work of <a href="http://worldbicyclerelief.org/pages/about" target="_blank">World Bicycle Relief</a> firsthand.</p>\r\n<h4>Reception &amp; Auction:</h4>\r\n<p>Thursday, November 29th<br />\r\n<a href="http://cedarlakedance.com" target="_blank">Cedar Lake Theatre</a><br />\r\n<a href="#gMap" class="gMap" title="Cedar Lake Theatre">547 West 26th Street<br />\r\nNew York, NY 10001</a></p>', 'SRAM pART PROJECT transforms bike parts into art that makes a difference and a big splash, too.', 1, '2012-09-09 00:00:00', '2012-09-09', '2014-05-31 05:53:44'),
(7, 'washington-square-outdoor-art-exhibit', 'Exhibition &amp; Sale: Washington Square', '', '', '', '<h3>FALL 2010 Labor Day Weekend</h3>\r\n<p>It''s a twice-a-year happening every Memorial Day Weekend and the weekend that follows and every Labor Day Weekend and the weekend that follows that. The event showcases fine artists and craft artisans from around the New York metropolitan area, the nation and the world. Attendees come from all over and are a cosmopolitan mix, including art lovers, tourists, faculty and students from the area''s many schools and professionals such as interior designers. I''ll be selling!</p>\r\n<p>Days: <strong>September 4, 5, 6, and September 11, 12</strong> (I''m participating only on the 4th and 6th)<br />\r\nExhibit Hours:<strong> Noon - 6 p.m. every show day</strong> Location: <strong>Washington Square Park</strong> @ Washington Square East NY NY 10003. Near the West 4th, Astor Place and 8th st subway stops <a href="http://bit.ly/d0jJ4g">- see map</a>. My booth will probably be on University Place near 8th street.</p>\r\n<h4>Exhibit Categories:</h4>\r\n<p>Graphics, Mixed Media, Oils &amp; Acrylic, Watercolor Photography, Sculpture, Crafts<br />\r\nJewelry, Metal Work, Ceramics, Glass Mixed Media, Fiber, Wood</p>\r\n<p>The show has its venue on University Place, starting at East 10th Street and extending south along the east side of Washington Square Park to West 3rd Street. The southern end of the show encompasses Schwartz Plaza, also known as Bobkin Lane, between NYU''s Shimkin Hall and Bobst Library.</p>\r\n<p>Get <a href="http://www.washingtonsquareoutdoorartexhibit.org/home.php">more information on the event</a> and <a href="http://www.washingtonsquareoutdoorartexhibit.org/visitorsguide.php">visitor''s info</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.washingtonsquareoutdoorartexhibit.org/home.php"><img src="http://www.baralaye.com/images/email/Labor-Day-show_2010/crowds.jpg" alt="The Washington Square Outdoor Art Exhibit 2010 Spring Show" /></a><br />\r\nPhotography by Rebecca MB. Pearson</p>', 'The Washington Square Art Sale showcases fine artists and craft artisans from around the New York metropolitan area, the nation and the world.', 1, '2010-08-16 00:00:00', '2010-08-16', '2014-05-31 13:58:37'),
(8, '1stdibs-2012', 'Exhibition: 1stDibs Solo', '/images/post/1stdibs-2012.jpg', '1stDibs Show', '', '<p>I am having an exhibition of new work at <a href="http://1stdibs.com" target="_blank">1stDibs</a>, presented by <a href="http://stellarunion.com" target="_blank">Stellar Union</a>. Some of my recent sculptures and drawings will be on display. All are invited and encouraged to see the show. Details are below.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://1stdibs.com" target="_blank">1stDibs / NY Design Center</a><br />\r\n<a href="http://g.co/maps/r4hge" target="_blank">200 Lexington Ave. 10th Floor<br />\r\nNew York, NY 10016</a></p>\r\n<p>Opening reception: May 5th (Saturday), 3-5pm<br />\r\nExhibition duration: May 5th - 30th, 2012<br />\r\nOpen to the public: Monday - Friday: 9:30AM - 5:30PM, Saturday: 10AM - 5PM</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.1stdibs.com/introspective/on_location/ebitenyefa_baralaye/" target="_blank"> See my 1stDibs Interview.</a></p>', 'I am having an exhibition of new work at 1stDibs, presented by Stellar Union. Some of my recent sculptures and drawings will be on display.', 1, '2010-04-08 00:00:00', '2010-04-08', '2014-05-31 14:00:26'),
(9, 'csg-narthex-art-2011', 'Exhibition: Calvary St. George&apos;s', '/images/post/csg-2011.jpg', 'Calvary Narthex Exhibition', '', '<p>On Sunday September 11th  I&rsquo;ll have the privilege of opening an exhibition of works, my first solo show, at <a href="http://www.calvarystgeorges.org" target="_blank">Calvary St. George''s Parish</a>&nbsp;in conjunction with their <a href="http://www.calvarystgeorges.org/news/2011/september/parish-september-11th-service" target="_blank">memorial service</a> observing the tragedy our nation suffered a decade ago. A selection of my <a href="/sculpture">sculptures</a> and <a href="/drawings">sketches</a> will be on display commencing the parish''s&nbsp;<a href="http://www.calvarystgeorges.org/news/2011/september/calvary-st-georges-arts-program" target="_blank">Narthex Art</a> series. The narthex series promotes visual art as a catalyst to spiritual worship and empowers artists to engage spiritual identity as a formative element of creativity and as a service to community. See details below.</p>\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.calvarystgeorges.org/news/2011/september/calvary-st-georges-arts-program" target="_blank">Narthex Art Exhibition</a></h4>\r\n<p>Duration: 9/11/2011 ~ 10/2/2011 (reception: 9/11 noon ~ 1pm).<br />\r\nVisiting Hours: Weekly Sunday through Friday, noon ~ 1pm.<br />\r\nVenue: <a href="http://bit.ly/rsOEGk" target="_blank">Cavalry Parish &ndash; 277 Park Avenue South @ East 21st Street</a>.</p>', 'On Sunday September 11th I&apos;ll have the privilege of opening an exhibition of works, my first solo show, at Calvary St. George''s Parish in conjunction with their memorial service observing the tragedy our nation suffered a decade ago.', 1, '2011-09-10 00:00:00', '2011-09-10', '2014-05-31 14:11:36'),
(10, 'csg-narther-art-inaugural-exhibition', 'Exhibition: CSG Narthex Art Inaugural', '/images/post/full/csg-narthex-art_inaugural_p.jpg', 'CSG Narther Art Inaugural Exhibition', '', '<p>\r\n<a href="http://calvarystgeorges.org/artsministry" target="_blank">Narthex Art at Calvary Church</a> Inaugural Group Show.\r\nFeaturing work by Ebitenyefa Baralaye, David Chang, Anna Coleman and Mark Samuel.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n7/15/2012 through 9/12/2012<br />\r\n277 Park Avenue South @ East 21st St 10010<br />\r\nOpen: Sundays and weekdays, noon - 1pm. Closed Saturdays.\r\n</p>', 'Narthex Art at Calvary Church Inaugural Group Show. Featuring work by Ebitenyefa Baralaye, David Chang, Anna Coleman and Mark Samuel.', 1, '2012-07-18 00:00:00', '2012-07-18', '2014-05-31 05:52:39'),
(11, 'excalibur-bronze-foundry-sculpture-2010-opening-and-show', 'Exhibition: Excalibur Bronze Foundry | Sculpture 2010', '', '', '', '<p><strong>Opening Date:</strong> Saturday, May 1, 2010 | 6:00pm - 9:00pm<br />\r\n<strong>Show Duration:</strong> May 3rd to May 14th 2010<br />\r\n<strong>Location:</strong> <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=309+Starr+Street+Brooklyn,+NY+11237&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=34.671324,79.013672&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=309+Starr+St,+Brooklyn,+Kings,+New+York+11237&amp;z=16">Excalibur Bronze Sculpture Foundry 309 Starr Street Brooklyn, NY</a></p>\r\n<p>Join us for the opening party of the 1st Annual Juried Group Sculpture Exhibition and see the Foundry team pour 2000 degree molten bronze - a rare opportunity to witness the ancient process of lost wax bronze casting during the 1st ever Excalibur Candlelight Pour!</p>\r\n<p><a href="/images/misc/Excalibur_Sculpture_2010_poster.jpg">See the event poster!</a></p>', 'Join us for the opening party of the 1st Annual Juried Group Sculpture Exhibition and see the Foundry team pour 2000 degree molten bronze - a rare opportunity to witness the ancient process of lost wax bronze casting during the 1st ever Excalibur Candlelight Pour!', 1, '2010-04-21 00:00:00', '2010-04-21', '2014-05-31 13:59:06'),
(12, 'gyeonggi-international-ceramix-biennale-2011', 'Exhibition: Gyeonggi International Ceramix Biennale', '/images/post/gicb-2011.jpg', 'Cavalry Narthex Exhibition', '', '<p>My sculpture piece <a href="/sculpture/adesuwa" target="_blank">Adesuwa</a>, fondly dedicated to my mother, will be on exhibit at the <a href="http://www.wocef.com/eng/03_biennale/2011/03_02.asp" target="_blank">Gyeonggi International Ceramix Biennale 2011</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gyeonggi-do" target="_blank">Gyeonggi-do Province</a> of  Korea. During the biennale I have also been invited to participate in an onsite <a href="http://www.wocef.com/eng/03_biennale/2011/03_06.asp" target="_blank">international exchange workshop</a> gathering artists from all over the world together to celebrate and explore the rich possibilities of ceramic art through varied cultural, aesthetic and technical approaches. I am very much looking forward to it. Details are below.</p>\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.wocef.com/eng/03_biennale/2011/03_02.asp" target="_blank">Ceramix Biennale &ldquo;Journey From the Fire&rdquo;</a></h4>\r\n<p>Duration: Sept. 24 ~ Nov. 22, 2011 (Opening ceremony: Sept. 23)<br />\r\nVenues: Icheon, Gwangju, Yeoju</p>\r\n<h4><a href="http://www.wocef.com/eng/03_biennale/2011/03_06.asp" target="_blank">International Artist Exchange</a></h4>\r\n<p>Duration: Sept. 24 ~ Oct. 3, 2011<br />\r\nVenues: Icheon, Gwangju and Yeoju</p>', 'My sculpture piece Adesuwa, fondly dedicated to my mother, will be on exhibit at the Gyeonggi International Ceramix Biennale 2011 in the Gyeonggi-do Province of Korea.', 1, '2011-09-10 00:00:00', '2011-09-10', '2014-05-31 05:58:48'),
(13, 'moscow-clayworks-show', 'Exhibition: Moscow Clayworks', '', '', '', '<p>In 2006 I did a summer assistantship at <a href="http://www.pvcrafts.org">Peters Valley Craft Center</a>''s ceramics department that significantly pushed my sense of creative freedom as an artist. In the woods of the valley, surrounded by the dust of clay and the smoke of fiery kilns, I produced what ultimately became the first models of my recently completed bronze series. I also had the pleasure of meeting and being inspired by many artists, namely the head of Peters Valley''s ceramics department, <a href="http://www.pvcrafts.org/who/bruce_dehnert-pix.htm">Bruce Dehnert</a>. At <a href="http://www.moscowclayworks.com">Moscow Clayworks</a> Bruce has organized a show of works from assistants he has overseen through his tenure. I will be exhibiting my piece, <a href="http://baralaye.com/sculpture/jonah">Jonah</a>. For those of you who can make it out to Moscow PA or live nearby, you are encouraged to attend the show. It''s a delightful display of artwork from a diverse range of artists.  Details are below:</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.moscowclayworks.com">Moscow Clayworks</a><br />\r\nSunday, July 17th 2011 - September 2011<br />\r\n<a href="http://bit.ly/o1Mdpg">223 N. Main St. Moscow. PA. 18444</a></p>', 'In 2006 I did a summer assistantship at Peters Valley Craft Center''s ceramics department. I produced what ultimately became the first models of my recently completed bronze series.', 1, '2011-07-17 00:00:00', '2011-07-17', '2014-05-31 06:02:02'),
(14, 'osilas-gallery-2012', 'Exhibition: OSilas Gallery | Journey of Faith', '/images/post/osilas-gallery-2012.jpg', 'OSilas Gallery | Journey of Faith', '', '<p>This fall at <a href="http://osilasgallery.org" target="_blank">OSilas Gallery</a> the relationships between religion and art will be featured in the exhibition <a href="http://osilasgallery.org/2012/07/18/journey-of-faith/" target="_blank">Journey of Faith</a>. The exhibition will highlight the creation of visual interpretations of Christian faith.</p>\r\n<p>Participating artists include: Elena Agostinis, La Thoriel Badenhausen, <strong>Ebitenyefa Baralaye</strong>, Joseph Dermody, Randy Frost, David Galalis, Mary Mihelic, Michelle Arnold Paine, Leslie Pelino, Luis Perelman, Gene Schmidt, Vadis Turner, and Joanna Wezyk</p>\r\n<h4>Reception:</h4>\r\n<p>Friday, September 14th, 7pm (Reception) - Oct 14th</p>\r\n<h4>Gallery Talk:</h4>\r\n<p>Sunday, September 23, 12:30pm<br />\r\nThe Image of Jesus in Art Across Time<br />\r\nPatricia Pongracz &ndash; Acting Director of <a href="http://www.mobia.org" target="_blank"> Museum of Biblical Art</a><br />\r\nReservations Required. Call 914.395.4520 to RSVP.</p>\r\n<h4>Location:</h4>\r\n<p><a href="http://osilasgallery.org">OSilas Gallery</a> at Concordia College, NY<br />\r\n<small>The gallery is located in the Donald A Krenz Academic Center on the second level of Scheele Memorial Library</small><br />\r\n<a href="#gMap" class="gMap" title="Osilas Gallery">171 White Plains Rd, Bronxville, NY 10708</a></p>\r\n<h4>Gallery Hours:</h4>\r\n<p>Tuesday - Friday, 12:00pm - 5:00pm<br />\r\nThursday 12:00am - 7:00pm<br />\r\nSaturday &amp; Sunday, 2:00pm - 5:00pm</p>', 'This fall at OSilas Gallery the relationships between religion and art will be featured in the exhibition Journey of Faith. The exhibition will highlight the creation of visual interpretations of Christian faith.', 1, '2012-09-11 00:00:00', '2012-09-11', '2014-05-30 23:50:00'),
(15, 'redeemmer-i-harvest-art-show', 'Exhibition: Redeemer | I Harvest ', '', '', '', '<h2>I Harvest</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://www.faithandwork.org/exhibitions_page1378.php">http://www.faithandwork.org/exhibitions_page1378.php</a><br />\r\n2009 Annual Juried Exhibition<br />\r\nOctober 16, 2009 - early January 2010<br />\r\nRedeemer offices, 1359 Broadway, Suite 400<br />\r\n<br />\r\n"The harvest is plentiful but the workers are few. Ask the Lord of the harvest, therefore, to send out workers into his harvest field." Matthew 9:37, 38<br />\r\n<br />\r\nExhibition Opening Party and Art Sale!<br />\r\nFriday, October 16, 6:00-9:00pm<br />\r\nEnjoy GREAT ART, food, music, and more! All artwork discounted 10%, one night only!<br />\r\nProceeds benefit Redeemer''s RENEW Campaign. No RSVP required.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRedeemer''s artists are working in God''s harvest field for the renewal of our culture. Feed on the fruits of their labor at our annual Juried Exhibition, showing from October 16 through early January 2010. See more than 50 works created by artists in Redeemer''s extended community.</p>', 'Redeemer''s artists are working in God''s harvest field for the renewal of our culture. Feed on the fruits of their labor at our annual Juried Exhibition, showing from October 16 through early January 2010. ', 1, '2009-10-15 00:00:00', '2009-10-15', '2014-05-31 14:07:42'),
(16, 'space-womb-amalgamation', 'Exhibition: Space Womb Gallery | Amalgamation', '/images/post/full/space-womb_amalgamation.jpg', 'Space Womb Gallery', '', '<p><a href="http://spacewombgallery.com" target="_blank">Space Womb gallery</a> announces upcoming group exhibition: amalgamation.</p>\r\n<h4>Opening Reception:</h4>\r\n<p>October 6th, 2012, 6-8pm</p>\r\n<h4>Exhibition Dates:</h4>\r\n<p>October 6th - 19th, 2012</p>\r\n<h4><a href="http://spacewombgallery.com" target="_blank">Space Womb Gallery</a></h4>\r\n<p><a href="#gMap" class="gMap" title="Space Womb Gallery">22-48 Jackson Avenue<br />\r\nLong Island City, NY 11101</a>\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Gallery Hours:</h4>\r\n<p>Monday, Tuesday, Thursday - Sunday<br />\r\n12:00pm - 6:00pm</p>', 'Space Womb gallery announces upcoming group exhibition: amalgamation. Opening Reception: October 6th, 2012, 6-8pm', 1, '2012-09-27 00:00:00', '2012-09-27', '2014-05-30 23:48:56'),
(17, 'space-womb-fill-the-space-exhibition', 'Exhibition: Space Womb Gallery | Fill the Space', '/images/post/full/space-womb_fill-the-space.jpg', 'Space Womb Fill the Space Exhibition', '', '<p><a href="http://www.spacewomb.com" target="_blank">SPACEWOMb Gallery</a> is pleased to announce Salon Show &ldquo;FILL THE SPACE&rdquo;, â€¨a group exhibition featuring the works of emerging artists around the world.</p>\r\n<p>The purpose of the show is to bring the various contemporary art works together and discover brand new sensation throughout them. The exhibition will be held at SPACEWOMb Gallery,\r\nlocated at 11-48 Jackson Avenue #1, Long Island City, New York.</p>\r\n<p>Exhibition Dates : July 14th-26th<br />\r\nOpening Reception : July 21th, 6-8pm</p>', 'SPACEWOMb Gallery is pleased to announce Salon Show &quot;FILL THE SPACE&quot;, a group exhibition featuring the works of emerging artists around the world.', 1, '2012-07-18 00:00:00', '2012-07-18', '2014-05-31 14:12:27'),
(18, 'white-stone-gallery-exhibit-2012', 'Exhibition: White Stone Gallery | Fine Art &amp; Faith', '/images/post/wsg-ff-exhibit-2012.jpg', 'White Stone Gallery | Fine Art &amp; Faith Exhibit', '', '<p>I''m glad to be one of the selected artists in White Stone Gallery''s upcoming annual <a href="http://whitestonegallery.com/juriednews.php" target="_blank">Fine Art &amp; Faith Exhibit</a>. My piece, <a href="/sculpture/david">David</a>, will be on display. If you can make it out to the Philly area do drop by to check out the show. See details below.</p>\r\n<p>White Stone Gallery<br />\r\n<a id="gMap_addr" class="ltbx gMap" href="#gMap" title="White Stone Gallery">4219 Main Street<br />\r\nPhiladelphia, PA 19127</a></p>\r\n<p>Duration: January 14 - February 4, 2012<br />\r\nOpen: Wednesday - Saturday, 11am - 6pm and by appointment</p>', 'I''m glad to be one of the selected artists in White Stone Gallery''s upcoming annual Fine Art & Faith Exhibit.', 1, '2011-12-24 00:00:00', '2011-12-24', '2014-05-31 05:56:38'),
(19, 'going-to-china', 'Going to China', '', '', '', '<p>I&rsquo;m excitedly looking forward to my first international art residency this summer. As a part of <a href="http://air-projects.org/programs/beijing/residency/" target="_blank">AIR Projects Beijing</a> I&rsquo;ll be travelling to China and dwelling in North East of Beijing between the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caochangdi" target="_blank">Caochangdi</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/798_Art_Zone" target="_blank">798 Art District</a> neighborhoods. Over the course of roughly a month from July 6th to August 3rd 2011, I along with a group of other artists will be immersing ourselves in Chinese culture, one rich in the arts, both traditional and modern. We&rsquo;ll be making art, visiting artist studios, institutions and galleries, and participating in critiques and lectures.</p>\r\n<p>This will be my first trip outside of the United States since entering in the late eighties. I&rsquo;m expectant of rich/challenging development in professional and personal discovery through this global exposure. I also plan on eating a lot of authentic Chinese food. I&rsquo;ll be posting regular updates via my blog throughout my stay.</p>\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re interested in coming <a href="http://air-projects.org/programs/beijing/apply/" target="_blank">applications are still being accepted.</a></p>', '', 25, '2011-05-12 00:00:00', '2011-05-12', '2014-05-31 06:06:11'),
(20, 'easter', 'Happy Easter &amp; Passover', '/images/post/full/caravaggio_thomas.jpg', 'The Incredulity of Saint Thomas - Caravaggio, 1601', '<a href="/images/post/full/caravaggio_thomas.jpg" class="ltbx" title="The Incredulity of Saint Thomas - Caravaggio, 1601">&quot;The Incredulity of Saint Thomas&quot; - Caravaggio, 1601.</a>', '<p>It&apos;s my favorite time of year, celebrating one man''s death and in it his gift of eternal renewal to many. I wish all of you a joyful Easter and Passover season.</p>\r\n<p>Verily, verily, I say unto you, Except a corn of wheat fall into the ground and die, it abideth alone: but if it die, it bringeth forth much fruit. - John 12:24 (KJV)</p>', 'It''s my favorite time of year, celebrating one man''s death and in it his gift of eternal renewal to many. I wish all of you a joyful Easter and Passover season.', 1, '2012-04-08 00:00:00', '2012-04-08', '2014-05-31 05:55:59'),
(22, '1stdibs-interview', 'Interview: 1stDibs', '/images/post/1stdibs-interview.jpg', '1stDibs Show', 'By Julie Baumgardner. <a href="http://www.1stdibs.com/introspective/on_location/ebitenyefa_baralaye/" target="_blank">Read the full article +.</a>', '<p>\r\nBut he accentuates the words he particularly wants you to hear: Nature. Humanity. Identity. These inform his expressive drawings and his sculptures realized primarily in ceramic but also , more recently, in bronze, plaster, nickel and wood. Throughout his work, abstraction reigns. Baralaye says the style allows him to &quot;explore the diversity of identity by non limiting each individual personality but by capturing its essence hollistically.&quot; <a href="http://www.1stdibs.com/introspective/on_location/ebitenyefa_baralaye/" target="_blank" class="more">Read More</a></p>', 'Ebitenyefa Baralaye speaks softly but he accentuates the words he particularly wants you to hear: Nature. Humanity. Identity.', 1, '2012-05-08 00:00:00', '2012-05-08', '2014-05-31 05:55:21'),
(23, 'jfj-benefit-art-auction', 'JfJ Benefit &amp; Art Auction', '', '', '', '<p>You are invited and requested to support a special cause at a fundraiser event this December 17th. In late August a college buddy of mine, Justin Yuen, was diagnosed with a very rare combination of leukemia and a germ cell tumor in his lungs. Raised in West Hartford CT, Justin studied Illustration at the Rhode Island School of Design, worked as a designer in NYC and had been living and working in Honk Kong when he got admitted with severe symptoms to an E.R. in the U.S. over a business trip. He&rsquo;s currently being hospitalized in NYC&rsquo;s Sloan Kettering Cancer Center after having undergone a successful and critical surgical operation. In and out of ICU and facing still much treatment ahead, Justin is keeping a positive spirit through it all. Unfortunately, none of the hefty expenses for his health treatment are being covered by insurance. So, Justin&rsquo;s friends and I have engaged a fundraising effort, &ldquo;Journey for Justin,&rdquo; to help him with the bill.</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;re going to be having a fundraising event in NYC on Friday December 17th that will include an art auction of fine art and design items/accessories, tasty refreshments and live music. Justin will also be calling in to say hello and express his thanks! Come help support our cause while mingling with friends and enjoying the evening&rsquo;s entertainment.</p>\r\n<h4><a target="_blank" href="http://bit.ly/jfj-nyc">JfJ Benefit &amp; Silent Art Auction</a></h4>\r\n<p>Friday December 17th | 6:30 - 9:30 PM<br />\r\n@ Salt Space - 1158 Broadway (by 27th St) 5th fl, NY NY 10024 | <a target="_blank" href="http://bit.ly/saltspace">map</a><br />\r\n$5 suggested donation at the door.<br />\r\n<a target="_blank" href="http://bit.ly/jfj-nyc-fb">Facebook rsvp</a></p>\r\n<p>*The art auction will feature works by VengRWK, street artist Choice Royce, and graphic artist Abe Lincoln Jr., along with RISD Alumni.</p>\r\n<p>Do bring your friends along and pass this invitation around to any others who would have interest.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you! We look forward to seeing you and very much appreciate your help.</p>\r\n<p><strong>For more information visit:</strong><br />\r\n<a target="_blank" href=" http://justlive.posterous.com">Justin&rsquo;s personal blog</a><br />\r\n<a target="_blank" href="http://journeyforjustin.com">Justin&rsquo;s fundraising website</a><br />\r\n<a target="_blank" href="http://tinyurl.com/journeyforjustin">Justin&rsquo;s Facebook group</a></p>\r\n<p>All the Best<br />\r\nEbi</p>', 'You are invited and requested to support a special cause at a fundraiser event this December 17th.', 0, '2010-12-10 00:00:00', '2010-12-10', '2014-05-31 13:55:50'),
(24, 'merry-christmas', 'Merry Christmas &amp; Happy New Year', '/images/post/merry-christmas.jpg', 'Nativity with Saints Francis and Lawrence - Caravaggio, 1609.', '<a class="ltbx" href="/images/post/caravaggio-nativity.jpg">"Nativity with Saints Francis and Lawrence" - Caravaggio,  1609.</a>', '<p>I''m wishing a blessed Christmas and a joyous New Year to all of you. Thank you for your continued encouragement and support.</p>', 'I''m wishing a blessed Christmas and a joyous New Year to all of you. Thank you for your continued encouragement and support.', 1, '2011-12-21 00:00:00', '2011-12-21', '2014-05-31 05:57:16'),
(25, 'merry-christmas-2012', 'Merry Christmas &amp; Happy New Year', '/images/post/caravaggio_adoration.jpg', 'Adoration of the Shepherds - Caravaggio, 1609.', '<a class="ltbx" href="/images/post/full/Adoration-of-the-Shepherds_Caravaggio_1609.jpg">"Adoration of the Shepherds" - Caravaggio,  1609.</a>', '<p>I''m wishing a blessed Christmas and a joyous new year to all of you. Thank you for your continued encouragement and support.</p>', 'I''m wishing a blessed Christmas and a joyous new year to all of you. Thank you for your continued encouragement and support.', 1, '2012-12-25 00:00:00', '2012-12-25', '2014-05-31 15:51:33'),
(26, 'merry-christmas-2013', 'Merry Christmas &amp; Happy New Year', '/images/post/caravaggio_adoration.jpg', 'Adoration of the Shepherds - Caravaggio, 1609.', '<a class="ltbx" href="/images/post/full/Adoration-of-the-Shepherds_Caravaggio_1609.jpg">"Adoration of the Shepherds" - Caravaggio,  1609.</a>', '<p>I''m wishing a blessed Christmas and a joyous new year to all of you. Thank you for your continued encouragement and support.</p>', 'I''m wishing a blessed Christmas and a joyous new year to all of you. Thank you for your continued encouragement and support.', 1, '2013-12-25 00:00:00', '2013-12-25', '2014-05-31 15:51:24'),
(27, 'moved-to-efa', 'New Studio: The Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts', '', '', '', '<p>I am proud and blessed to now be a part of the arts community at the <a href="http://efanyc.com" target="_blank">Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts</a>. Since moving in on April 1st, I&rsquo;ve taken very well to the warmth and friendliness of fellow professional artists in the building and even the bustling energy of the surrounding neighborhood of Times Square. My studio has a lovely view and is finally in working order after an initial few days of configuration and setup. I feel inspired and well underway with new ventures in my artwork and refreshed to finish existing pieces.  I&rsquo;m looking forward to the years ahead. My next goal will be organizing a solo show.</p>', 'I am proud and blessed to now be a part of the arts community at the Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts. ', 1, '2011-05-12 00:00:00', '2011-05-12', '2014-05-31 06:05:06'),
(28, 'peters-valley-2011', 'New Works: Ceramics from Peters Valley', '/images/post/anagama-kiln.jpg', 'Peters Valley 2011', '', '<p>In August I participated in an anagama workshop at <a href="http://pvcrafts.org" target="_blank">Peters Valley Craft Center</a>. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anagama_kiln" target="_blank">Anagama</a> is a traditional Japanese hillside ceramic kiln and firing process in which ash and flame from wood used to fuel the kiln over several (4-8) days forms the glaze and surface treatment of the works inside.  I&rsquo;m particularly drawn to the sweeping variation of earth tones and textures that come about fortuitously in response to the form of a piece, it&rsquo;s kiln position and the firing style, a symbiotic interplay that yields beautifully dynamic results. From this workshop I&rsquo;ve produced multiple <a href="/sculpture">sculptures</a> and <a href="/vessels">vessels</a> as additions to my portfolio.</p>', 'In August I participated in an anagama workshop at Peters Valley Craft Center. Anagama is a traditional Japanese hillside ceramic kiln and firing process in which ash and flame from wood used to fuel a kiln form the glaze of works.', 1, '2011-09-10 00:00:00', '2011-09-10', '2014-05-31 06:00:52'),
(29, 'efa-open-house-armory-2103', 'Open House: Elizabeth Foundation / Armory Arts Week 2013', '/images/post/efa-open-studio.jpg', 'Elizabeth Foundation Armory Open Studio 2012', '', '<p class="italic">"In celebration of the city''s unparalleled artistic communities, <a href="http://armoryartsweek.com" target="_blank">Armory Arts Week</a> highlights a neighborhood or borough''s arts scene each night with events."</p>\r\n<p>As part of <a href="http://armoryartsweek.com" target="_blank">Armory Arts Week</a>, we invite you to view nearly 60 <a href="http://efanyc.org" target="_blank">EFA</a> Open Studios and visit the <a href="http://efanyc.org/project-space-mission/" target="_blank">EFA Project Space</a> and <a href="http://efanyc.org/rbpmw/" target="_blank">Robert Blackburn Printmaking Workshop</a>. <a href="http://efanyc.org/armory-arts-week" targe="_blank">More details</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://efanyc.org/studio-members/" target="_blank">EFA Studios member artists</a> work in a wide range of media and artistic sensibilities, creating a vibrant and diverse community of peers under one roof. Artists on floors 3-10 will have their studios open to welcome guests to explore, interact, and investigate their art.</p>\r\n<p class="small">- Copy edited from <a href="http://efanyc.org/armory-arts-week" target="_blank">efanyc</a> -</p>\r\n<h4>Location:</h4>\r\n<p><a herf="http://efanyc.org" target="_blank">Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts</a><br />\r\n<a href="#gMap" class="gMap" title="Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts">323 West 39th St, Studio 914<br />\r\nNew York, NY 10018</a></p>\r\n<h4>Open to the public:</h4>\r\n<p>Saturday, March 9th, 1:00 &ndash; 6:00pm</p>', 'As part of Armory Arts Week, we invite you to view nearly 60 EFA Open Studios and visit the EFA Project Space and Robert Blackburn Printmaking Workshop.', 1, '2013-03-08 00:00:00', '2013-03-08', '2014-05-30 23:47:04'),
(30, 'efa-armory-open-house-2014', 'Open House: EFA Armory Arts Week', '/images/post/efa-open-studio.jpg', 'Elizabeth Foundation Armory Open Studio 2012', '', '<p>As part of <a href="http://armoryartsweek.com" target="_blank">Armory Arts Week</a> you are invited to the <a href="http://efanyc.org" targe="_blank">Elizabeth Foundation</a> to visit my studio and many other <a href="http://efanyc.org/armory-arts-week/" targe="_blank">artist studios</a> as well as the <a href="http://efanyc.org/project-space-mission/" target="_blank">EFA Project Space</a> and the<a href="http://efanyc.org/rbpmw/" target="_blank">Robert Blackburn Printmaking Workshop</a>. Refreshments, art and good company will be enjoyed. See the details below.</p>\r\n<p><em>"<a href="http://efanyc.org/studio-members/" target="_blank">EFA Studios member artists</a> work in a wide range of media and artistic sensibilities, creating a vibrant and diverse community of peers under one roof. Artists on floors 3-10 will have their studios open to welcome guests to explore, interact, and investigate their art."</em> - <a href="http://efanyc.org/armory-arts-week" target="_blank">EFA</a></p>\r\n<h4>Location:</h4>\r\n<p><a href="/map" target="_blank">Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts<br />\r\n323 West 39th St, Studio 914<br />\r\nNew York, NY 10018</a></p>\r\n<h4>Open to the public:</h4>\r\n<p>Saturday, March 8th, 1:00 &ndash; 6:00pm</p>', 'As part of Armory Arts Week you are invited to the Elizabeth Foundation to visit my studio and many other artist studios as well as the EFA Project Space and theRobert Blackburn Printmaking Workshop.', 1, '2014-03-05 00:00:00', '2014-03-05', '2014-05-31 15:50:01'),
(31, 'elizabeth-foundation-open-studio-2011', 'Open Studio: Elizabeth Foundation 2011', '/images/post/efa-open-studio.jpg', 'Elizabeth Foundation Open Studio 2011', '', '<p>You are welcomed to come and see the latest creations in my studio and the works and working places of a multitude of other wonderfully talented artists at the <a href="http://www.efanyc.org" target="_blank">Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts</a>. Refreshments will be provided.</p>\r\n<p>See <a href="http://www.efanyc.org/open-studios/" target="_blank">more details</a>, information on <a href="http://www.efanyc.org/studio-members/" target="_blank">participating artists</a> and <a href="http://www.efanyc.org/open-studios-2011-videos/" target="_blank">video tour previews</a>.</p>\r\n<h4><a herf="http://www.efanyc.org" id="gMap_title">Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts</a></h4>\r\n<p><a href="#gMap" class="ltbx" id="gMap_addr">323 West 39th St New York, NY 10018</a> Studio 914</p>\r\n<p>Thursday, October 13th (opening reception) 6 ~ 10 PM<br />\r\nFriday, October 14th 6 ~ 9 PM<br />\r\nSaturday, October 15th 1 ~ 6 PM</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<iframe width="675" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/YcRFceZvjHM" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'You are welcomed to come and see the latest creations in my studio and the works and working places of a multitude of other wonderfully talented artists at the Elizabeth Foundation for the Arts. ', 1, '2011-09-12 00:00:00', '2011-09-12', '2014-05-31 05:57:45');
